210b8094-6b51-4e44-9a8b-4bc5a560fa92	money	Money	"[{\\"id\\":\\"2407e200-e983-40eb-997d-dbb1a99094bb\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Paying for Stuff 🏦 \\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"896ceb4e-216d-40c3-a965-12db1da8b740\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"The easiest way to pay for things in Costa Rica is your credit card, all stores big and small will almost always take Credit Cards. Credit Cards will usually give you the best FX rate and you avoid having to deal with cash.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"e457b3fa-3103-4178-b51f-364f3e292822\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Getting Colones\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"9cc8a04e-605a-4d89-abc1-16a7074c3516\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Sometimes, you do need cash or you prefer it for other reasons. The best and easiest way to get Colones is to withdraw from the ATM. It will give you the best rate and you don't have to hold on to large amounts of cash. However your bank will likely charge you a fee for using international ATMs.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"1a7025c1-c216-4195-b554-0b8b775a9b1a\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"To avoid those ATM fees, you can open one of many no-fee accounts which will waive all those fees. For example, I use Fidelity Cash which is just a regular cash account in a US bank and I withdraw money from it without paying any fees. There are other options depending on your needs.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"d7009a3a-28a5-4e1b-ae56-39f4c3534ac5\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"There is usually a limit of how much you can withdraw in a given day, however I found that the Banco National ATM in San Mateo allows you to withdraw multiple times in the same day and somehow avoiding that limit. I've tested it by doing two 300k withdrawal transactions back-to-back without any issues, while officially my limit is less then that. Basically experiment!\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"e3b36b5b-a4fd-4451-b4cd-000910431651\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Using Dollars\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"7ba39533-080e-4f57-8819-f30c34b6a3c9\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"You will find that most vendors and even many stores accept dollars directly. Simply ask your vendor or store and see if they accept dollars. Also be sure to check their conversion rate, usually they will use the standard conversion rate as shown here.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"448ab795-4f6e-4edf-9074-b9a5757408c0\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Large Purchases\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"7a7d357a-847b-450a-a8ca-562d05d88ab1\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"If you need to make a large purchase such as a car, you will likely want to do an international wire. There will be a fee most likely that your bank charges depending on the type of account you have, there will also be a fee that the recipient bank will charge that you will not see, but your recipient will. There is no way to avoid the recipient fee, but you can find US banks that don't charge wire fees depending on the minimum balance you have in your account. For example the Chase Saphire Checking account will have no fees on wires and will also have no ATM or FX fees. \\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"5aaa14a4-211c-4e9f-9fed-c441e734f289\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"538a0682-68b5-43c1-84e7-a2aada637819\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Exchange Rates\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"057b5bae-ae07-43f6-afa7-5f93c98392f7\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Each bank will have its own rate when converting as well as an optional fee for doing a foreign currency transaction. The exchange rate you're getting will depend on the bank doing the currency conversion and they will always be worse then whatever is the official \\\\\\"Exchange Rate\\\\\\". \\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"c162a30c-55b7-4e15-9554-b226f0e48399\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"\\\\nIf you have your money in a local bank such as BN or similar, you can see the exchange rate that they will use to convert from USD to Colones here:\\\\n\\",\\"styles\\":{}},{\\"type\\":\\"link\\",\\"href\\":\\"https://gee.bccr.fi.cr/IndicadoresEconomicos/Cuadros/frmConsultaTCVentanilla.aspx\\",\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"https://gee.bccr.fi.cr/IndicadoresEconomicos/Cuadros/frmConsultaTCVentanilla.aspx\\",\\"styles\\":{}}]}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"6fb2b479-3373-49a1-bb4a-cb80ccfb2b39\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"\\\\\\"Compra\\\\\\" is the column you should be looking at for the exchange rate of your bank.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"0f563868-e4ab-40b3-956f-57a89e590060\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[],\\"children\\":[]}]"	A page about Money	2025-03-24 16:24:47.98089+00	2025-03-27 20:19:38.145+00	\N	f	Local Know-How	9	'-000910431651':376 '-3103':96 '-3373':811 '-4178':97 '-49':812 '/indicadoreseconomicos/cuadros/frmconsultatcventanilla.aspx':799,806 '057b5bae':672 '057b5bae-ae07-43f6-afa7-5f93c98392f7':671 '080e':399 '0b8b775a9b1a':208 '0f563868':850 '0f563868-e4ab-40b3-956f-57a89e590060':849 '12db1da8b740':35 '16a7074c3516':126 '1a7025c1':203 '1a7025c1-c216':202 '211c':627 '216d':32 '2407e200':3 '28a5':283 '3':19,111,387,479,641,661 '300k':348 '364f3e292