\\":\\"To avoid those ATM fees, you can open one of many no-fee accounts which will waive all those fees. For example, I use Fidelity Cash which is just a regular cash account in a US bank and I withdraw money from it without paying any fees. There are other options depending on your needs.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"d7009a3a-28a5-4e1b-ae56-39f4c3534ac5\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"There is usually a limit of how much you can withdraw in a given day, however I found that the Banco National ATM in San Mateo allows you to withdraw multiple times in the same day and somehow avoiding that limit. I've tested it by doing two 300k withdrawal transactions back-to-back without any issues, while officially my limit is less then that. Basically experiment!\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"e3b36b5b-a4fd-4451-b4cd-000910431651\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\",\\"level\\":3},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"Using Dollars\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"7ba39533-080e-4f57-8819-f30c34b6a3c9\\",\\"type\\":\\"paragraph\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlignment\\":\\"left\\"},\\"content\\":[{\\"type\\":\\"text\\",\\"text\\":\\"You will find that most vendors and even many stores accept dollars directly. Simply ask your vendor or store and see if they accept dollars. Also be sure to check their conversion rate, usually they will use the standard conversion rate as shown here.\\",\\"styles\\":{}}],\\"children\\":[]},{\\"id\\":\\"448ab795-4f6e-4edf-9074-b9a5757408c0\\",\\"type\\":\\"heading\\",\\"props\\":{\\"textColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"backgroundColor\\":\\"default\\",\\"textAlign